The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | New Bhel venture
                                                                                                               New Bhel venture
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                                            
	New Delhi, April 2: Bharat Heavy Electricals Ltd (Bhel) plans to invest Rs 1,200 crore in a joint venture with an international company to manufacture transmission equipment.        
	We are in talks with a European and a Japanese firm to form a transmission joint venture by June 2009, K. Ravi Kumar, chairman and managing director of Bhel, said.        
	Company officials said the firm was in talks with French equipment maker Areva and Toshiba of Japan for a joint venture in 765 kilo volt (KV) and 1,200KV transmission equipment. He said the company expected sales to grow 20-25 per cent by March 2010.         
	According to Ravi Kumar, the company has a Rs 50,000-crore order book and expects more contracts this month.        
	We are negotiating some contracts in April. For next year, we project an order book of Rs 50,000 crore, he said.                                                                                                                                        
